inputEventSource.name: InputEventSource
inputEventSource.description: Input source i.e. Mouse or API

timestamp.name: Timestamp
timestamp.description: iMotions synchronization timestamp. Relative to data recording start

eT_GazeLeftx.name: ET_GazeLeftx
eT_GazeLeftx.description: X-coordinate of the  gaze point (2D) of the left eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the computer screen)

eT_GazeLefty.name: ET_GazeLefty
eT_GazeLefty.description: Y-coordinate of the  gaze point (2D) of the left eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the computer screen)

eT_GazeRightx.name: ET_GazeRightx
eT_GazeRightx.description: X-coordinate of the gaze point (2D) of the right eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the computer screen)

eT_GazeRighty.name: ET_GazeRighty
eT_GazeRighty.description: Y-coordinate of the gaze point (2D) of the right eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the computer screen)

eT_PupilLeft.name: ET_PupilLeft
eT_PupilLeft.description: Pupil diameter of the left eye

eT_PupilRight.name: ET_PupilRight
eT_PupilRight.description: Pupil diameter of the right eye

eT_DistanceLeft.name: ET_DistanceLeft
eT_DistanceLeft.description: Estimated distance between the eye-tracker and the left eye

eT_DistanceRight.name: ET_DistanceRight
eT_DistanceRight.description: Estimated distance between the eye-tracker and the right eye

eT_CameraLeftX.name: ET_CameraLeftX
eT_CameraLeftX.description: X-coordinate of the left eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the eye-tracker's capture box)

eT_CameraLeftY.name: ET_CameraLeftY
eT_CameraLeftY.description: Y-coordinate of the left eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the eye-tracker's capture box)

eT_CameraRightX.name: ET_CameraRightX
eT_CameraRightX.description: X-coordinate of the right eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the eye-tracker's capture box)

eT_CameraRightY.name: ET_CameraRightY
eT_CameraRightY.description: Y-coordinate of the right eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the eye-tracker's capture box)

gaze X.name: Gaze X
gaze X.description: Gaze data X-coordinate (relative to top-left corner of the screen). Average of the X-coordinates of the left and right eye.

gaze Y.name: Gaze Y
gaze Y.description: Gaze data Y-coordinate (relative to top-left corner of the screen). Average of the Y-coordinates of the left and right eye.

interpolated Gaze X.name: Interpolated Gaze X
interpolated Gaze X.description: Gaze data X-coordinate (relative to top-left corner of the screen) with missing coordinates interpolated. Average of the X-coordinates of the left and right eye.

interpolated Gaze Y.name: Interpolated Gaze Y
interpolated Gaze Y.description: Gaze data Y-coordinate (relative to top-left corner of the screen) with missing coordinates interpolated. Average of the Y-coordinates of the left and right eye.

interpolated Distance.name: Interpolated Distance
interpolated Distance.description: Estimated distance between the eye-tracker and the eyes, with missing values interpolated. Average of the eye tracker's distance to the left and right eye.

gaze Velocity.name: Gaze Velocity
gaze Velocity.description: Angular velocity of the gaze at the current sample point, i.e. how fast the eyes are moving at this point in time.

gaze Acceleration.name: Gaze Acceleration
gaze Acceleration.description: Angular acceleration of the gaze at the current sample point, i.e. how much the eyes increased in speed at the current sample.

fixation Index.name: Fixation Index
fixation Index.description: Fixation number, counting from start of the recording.

fixation Index by Stimulus.name: Fixation Index by Stimulus
fixation Index by Stimulus.description: Fixation number, counting from start of the stimulus.

fixation X.name: Fixation X
fixation X.description: X-coordinate of the fixation centroid (relative to top-left corner of the screen).

fixation Y.name: Fixation Y
fixation Y.description: Y-coordinate of the fixation centroid (relative to top-left corner of the screen).

fixation Start.name: Fixation Start
fixation Start.description: Start time of the fixation (relative to recording start).

fixation End.name: Fixation End
fixation End.description: End time of the fixation (relative to recording start).

fixation Dispersion.name: Fixation Dispersion
fixation Dispersion.description: Dispersion of the fixation, i.e. how much the fixation's gaze points are spread out.

saccade Index.name: Saccade Index
saccade Index.description: Saccade number, counting from start of the recording.

saccade Index by Stimulus.name: Saccade Index by Stimulus
saccade Index by Stimulus.description: Saccade number, counting from start of the stimulus.

saccade Start.name: Saccade Start
saccade Start.description: Start time of the saccade (relative to recording start).

saccade End.name: Saccade End
saccade End.description: End time of the saccade (relative to recording start).

saccade Amplitude.name: Saccade Amplitude
saccade Amplitude.description: Amplitude of the saccade, i.e. angular distance that the eyes travelled from start point to end point.

saccade Peak Velocity.name: Saccade Peak Velocity
saccade Peak Velocity.description: Peak velocity of the saccade, i.e. the maximal speed of the eyes during this saccade.

saccade Peak Acceleration.name: Saccade Peak Acceleration
saccade Peak Acceleration.description: Peak acceleration of the saccade, i.e.  the maximal increase in speed of the eyes during this saccade.

saccade Peak Deceleration.name: Saccade Peak Deceleration
saccade Peak Deceleration.description: Peak deceleration of the saccade, i.e. the maximal decrease in speed of the eyes during this saccade.

saccade Direction.name: Saccade Direction
saccade Direction.description: Direction of the saccade from its start point to end point, indicated as counterclockwise angles: 0 degrees mean a horizontal saccade from left to right, 90 degrees a vertical saccade from bottom to top.

timestamp.name: Timestamp
timestamp.description: iMotions synchronization timestamp. Relative to data recording start
